<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/html">
<head>
  <script>
      ga('send', 'pageview', '/');
  </script>
</head>
<body>

<div class="row" id="hero">
  <video loop="loop" preload="auto" autoplay id="pretzel-video" class="video-playing">
    <source src="<%= asset_url 'lamp.mp4' %>" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="va-welcome">
    <h2>Welcome</h2>
    <h4>To Open Science</h4>
    <a href="/users/sign_up" class="btn hide-xs btn-contrast btn-large btn-semi-transparent js-show-how-it-works">
        Start Being Open
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row overview-panel text-center col-md-12 col-md-offset-0 col-xs-8 col-xs-offset-2">
<div class="community-overview col-md-6 col-xs-12">
  <span class="overview-icon mega-octicon octicon-organization"></span>

  <h4>Developing Community</h4>
  <p>Contribute thoughts, questions and reviews to published papers. Form research interest groups and collaborate with others.</p>
</div>
<div class="publication-overview col-md-6 col-xs-12">
  <span class="overview-icon mega-octicon octicon-book"></span>
  <h4>Research Management</h4>
  <p>Manage the evolution of your ideas, methods, and data. Keep a diary of papers you read. </p>
</div>
</div>


<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-8 col-sx-12">
    <hr>
    <h1 style="color: #337ab7">Open Science</h1>
    <p>
      Closed scientific communication creates unnecessary barriers in the way of progress, innovation, and
      transparency in research.
      <br>
      <br>
      ERDOS is aimed at those who believe that a better scientific communication model is possible. We provide:
    <ul class="about-points-list">
      <li type="square">A community to disseminate thoughts, ideas, and questions about published work</li>
      <li type="square">A management tool for the evolution of ideas, scripts, and results
      </li>
      <li type="square">A platform for post-publication review and citation analysis</li>
      <li type="square">An opportunity to maximise impact using qualitative metrics and analysis of open communication
      </li>
      <li type="square">Openness and transparency in research</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <hr>
    <div class="col-md-8 col-sx-12 pull-right" style="">
      <h1 style="color: #E36937">What's an Erdos?</h1>
      <p>
        Paul Erdős was one of the most prolific scientists
        and proponents of community
        science in the last century. He co-authored with over 500 collaborators throughout his career
        on some of the most important advances in mathematics in recent times. Like all great thinkers Erdős was
        something of an eccentric and we would like continue on in his tradition
        of thinking outside the box, putting science first, and leveraging the power of community in forwarding science.
      </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
  <hr>
  <img width="50" height="37" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;" src="<%= asset_path 'ef_logo.png' %>">

  <p>ERDOS Research is part of Entrepreneur First, Europe's foremost pre-seed startup
    incubator.</p>
</div>

</body>

<script>
    if (navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Android') >= 0) {
        document.getElementById('pretzel-video').controls = true;
    }

    window.addEventListener("scroll", function() {
        if (window.scrollY > 100) {
            $('.navbar').fadeOut();
        }
        else {
            $('.navbar').fadeIn();
        }
    },false);
</script>
</html>